<br>
Cleric is a great class.  The new changes proposed on test are well-meaning, but as I see it, will negate the contributions of Clerics to normal XP groups.  After all, who is going to want a cleric when you can have a druid who can 75% CH AND snare AND DOT AND evac if things get hairy (among other funtions) or a shaman who can 75% CH AND DOT AND buff AND slow AND haste... you get the picture.<br>
<br>
Talented Clerics know how to use the spells in their arsenal to do more than just &quot;sit and heal&quot;.  Stuns, Root, occasional nukes.. all are valuable tools in the Cleric lineup.  But when the chips are down, it's going to add up to &quot;who can do more for our group&quot;.<br>
 <p><center>k thx la~<br>
