<br>
Today I was fighting in OOT, late at night.  I and my necro companion died to a corrupted cyclops... it wasn't even close, he resisted the necro all over the place.  Well, I needed a rez, and no guild clerics were near... heck, we had only one online.  I mentioned what had happened though, and suddenly it hit me... our cleric was a human, and I'd given her a Freeport gatestone.  In 30 seconds she was within walking distance of OOT to rez us.  Nice!  <br>
<br>
But the story doesn't end there.  We decide we REALLY want this cyclops dead (no good reason, all the Dawn Rising druids in level range of epic had the item from him, and the necro was from an evil only guild, but we're crazy).  So now our cleric buffs me up... and we tank the little SoB without any problem at all.  Now, as a rogue, I can't get much agro when I can't backstab.  So after she buffs me up and meds, I get in the path of the cyclops, and she throws a celestial heal on me.  No agro yet, since I hadn't agroed it, but when I did I had about 14 seconds where I took  no damage (I was healing as much as I was being hit) with no agro anywhere... and no, druids do not get that kind of heal.  I keep tanking with patch heals a while, till the necro can land snare and fear, and then the fight is over, and one complete heal seals it up.  The modifications to druids and shamen don't cover these situations at all (heck, the druid couldn't even port closer).  <br>
<br>
And there is a case of a cleric doing much more than just medding and healing, this was a cleric thinking tactically, having the right tools up her sleave, and doing her job well.  I mean, a rogue would be boring as hell if I played Jarkell like some folks play clerics... what would I do, just backstab all day long in standard perfectly balanced exp groups?  BORING!  No, I solo giants because rogues aren't supposed to.  I fear kite.  I tank.  I sneak into rediculus places because I can.  I CR the bear pit in Voxes lair without SoW (try it some time, it can be done if you're clever).  <br>
<br>
And clerics can be wacky too.  Lord knows I've seen some real nice battle clerics out there, who have a good ole time (/tip hat to Hailhammer).  I've seen clerics with a good sense of humor, who are out there to have fun.  I've seen clerics get rezed by rogues (had to through that one out there, can't praise Hailhammer without taking a free shot!).  I've seen clerics tank.  Heck, I saw three clerics form an AoE exp group with a rogue (me) tanking!  By the way, they CAN do that well.<br>
<br>
Basically, any class can be boring if you just sit around and do tired old tactics that were figured out before Everquest left Beta.  You want to have fun with your class?  Make the most of it.  <br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvalquisssilverpalm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 437<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/27/02 7:48:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1284.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Whats missed</span><hr size=1> You think I want a druid in my group over a cleric, Captain?  Not likely!<br>
<br>
With a couple notable exceptions (Tuppen and Puddlefoot come to mind, great grouping druids!) the problem with druids isn't what spells they have, it's what they know and don't know.  Damn quad-kiting career soloists haven't got a clue about agro management, timing things in a group, and in many cases aren't even sure what to do when they do get agro and start running around waving their arms like bixies.<br>
<br>
Point is Captain, at least for a long time to come before these changes start affecting class selection from the ground up, it's still clerics who have chosen that path specifically because they want to heal.  Well, the half that aren't wannabe ubers.  And anyone who has chosen to be a healer because they like it is welcome in my groups anytime.<br>
